But back to the issue:<br>
<br>
responding to Zaph, nucl, and hamp above..<br>
<br>
<br>
Thats fine, but I still think it is a mistake to consider an essay on Earth-based power plants as being somehow having anything whatsover to do with promotion of space nuclear propulsion. And the fact that Greenpeace may find problems with the production and use of 238Pu has zero relationship to their disagreement with the current and proposed utilization of Earth-based fission technologies.<br>
<br>
I am vigorously opposed to the use of fission technologies in the biosphere. Yet I have much less (but definitely not zero) concerns with space-based fission technologies.<br>
<br>
Am ~I~ therefore a member of the &quot;Opposition&quot;??<br>
Heck no - as specified by the formal mission statement of this place, but yes, according to the &quot;collapsed catagories&quot; that have been reverted to.<br>
<br>
But again, Zaph may always organize as he chooses. I, as all other members are guests here.<br>
